00:42:37,012 --> 00:42:39,473
Right, I should. You never let me down.

531
00:42:39,557 --> 00:42:42,184
This is the Ma Hwi-yeong I know.
I'm relieved now.

532
00:42:42,476 --> 00:42:44,853
I have to say, you have a mind of steel.

533
00:42:44,937 --> 00:42:46,855
I really should learn that from you.

534
00:42:48,357 --> 00:42:50,859
I apologize for what my parents did

535
00:42:52,319 --> 00:42:53,445
to you and your father.

536
00:42:56,782 --> 00:42:59,243
But you and your family
have gotten enough out of this.

537
00:43:00,619 --> 00:43:01,912
So can't we call it even now?

538
00:43:06,709 --> 00:43:08,377
I'm impressed

539
00:43:08,460 --> 00:43:10,170
by how shameless you still are.

540
00:43:10,254 --> 00:43:11,880
Gosh, you and that ego of yours.

541
00:43:12,923 --> 00:43:14,758
You're really something.

542
00:43:14,842 --> 00:43:16,093
But you know what?

543
00:43:17,177 --> 00:43:18,679
I'm bored now.

544
00:43:19,221 --> 00:43:21,223
Studying is only fun

545
00:43:21,307 --> 00:43:23,684
when I have you

546
00:43:24,143 --> 00:43:26,562
competing fiercely against me as my rival.

547
00:43:28,689 --> 00:43:30,608
Who am I going to compete with
from now on?

548
00:43:34,153 --> 00:43:37,489
All right. Our government's
export-driven policy...

549
00:43:37,573 --> 00:43:39,408
-What's going on?
-Be quiet.

550
00:43:39,491 --> 00:43:40,868
Who are those people?

551
00:43:40,951 --> 00:43:43,078
They look like some high-ranking officers.

552
00:43:43,162 --> 00:43:44,163
Hey.

553
00:43:44,872 --> 00:43:46,165
-Pil-sang.
-Yes?

554
00:43:46,248 --> 00:43:47,499
I told you to be quiet.

555
00:43:48,167 --> 00:43:49,668
Ro-mi and I are going to the movies.

556
00:43:49,752 --> 00:43:51,545
Okay, sure. Stand straight, guys.

557
00:43:51,629 --> 00:43:53,005
In a fairly short amount of time,

558
00:43:53,088 --> 00:43:55,007
the focus shifted from light manufacturing

559
00:43:55,090 --> 00:43:58,969
to heavy, chemical,
and high-tech manufacturing.

560
00:43:59,053 --> 00:44:00,012
In this process,

561
00:44:00,095 --> 00:44:02,431
industrial facilities were mainly
built in the metropolitan area

562
00:44:02,514 --> 00:44:05,017
and the Yeongnam region.
Both had a lot of growth potential.

563
00:44:05,100 --> 00:44:06,560
"It pours out,

564
00:44:06,644 --> 00:44:09,521
collides against the rocks,
and fights fiercely."

565
00:44:09,605 --> 00:44:10,689
In this passage...

566
00:44:21,116 --> 00:44:22,117
Hello.

567
00:44:22,534 --> 00:44:23,994
We're from the Office of Education.

568
00:44:24,078 --> 00:44:25,788
Oh, welcome.

569
00:44:26,413 --> 00:44:28,248
-Hello.
-May we get started?

570
00:44:28,624 --> 00:44:30,584
Yes, sure.

571
00:44:37,049 --> 00:44:38,342
Mr. Oh.

572
00:44:38,967 --> 00:44:40,844
-Yes.
-We'll begin the investigation

573
00:44:40,928 --> 00:44:42,638
on the allegation that Ma Hwi-yeong

574
00:44:42,721 --> 00:44:44,890
had his grades tampered,
based on the statement made by

575
00:44:44,973 --> 00:44:46,725
his former homeroom teacher,
Mr. Kim Byeong-cheol.

576
00:44:46,809 --> 00:44:50,437
We'll also look into whether
any school violence took place

577
00:44:50,521 --> 00:44:52,731
and how it was dealt with if it did.

578
00:44:53,232 --> 00:44:56,110
In connection with the same student,
Ma Hwi-yeong.

579
00:44:57,611 --> 00:45:01,115
We'll need to interview a few students
during our investigation.

580
00:45:01,407 --> 00:45:04,034
The accused, Ma Hwi-yeong and Lee Gi-tae.

581
00:45:04,785 --> 00:45:06,912
And lastly, another student
of yours, Choe Jun-u.

582
00:45:08,831 --> 00:45:09,832
Sure.

583
00:45:10,332 --> 00:45:14,795
I'll answer all questions truthfully,
to the best of my knowledge.

584
00:45:16,797 --> 00:45:17,965
The thing is though,

585
00:45:18,799 --> 00:45:20,342
Hwi-yeong,

586
00:45:21,301 --> 00:45:23,804
as well as all other students,
are still very young.

587
00:45:24,513 --> 00:45:28,559
Please keep that in mind
and try to be considerate of them.

588
00:45:28,851 --> 00:45:29,977
Please.

589
00:45:31,395 --> 00:45:33,230
Could it have something to do
with those people?

590
00:45:33,313 --> 00:45:35,566
What's going on, So-ye?
Is there anything you know?

591
00:45:36,567 --> 00:45:37,901
Did they summon Gi-tae too?

592
00:45:41,321 --> 00:45:43,365
It's true that Hwi-yeong
asked me to do it,

593
00:45:45,617 --> 00:45:47,578
but paying them was my idea.

594
00:45:48,120 --> 00:45:50,456
They did ask for the money,

595
00:45:50,539 --> 00:45:53,709
but I wanted to impress Hwi-yeong as well.

596
00:46:01,258 --> 00:46:04,678
I told them everything. Now, I can
face you without feeling ashamed.

597
00:46:05,095 --> 00:46:07,848
And I apologized to Jun-u as well.

598
00:46:08,640 --> 00:46:11,560
That's great, Gi-tae.
You did the right thing.

599
00:46:12,895 --> 00:46:16,315
They'll interview me as well
because I'm your homeroom teacher.

600
00:46:16,398 --> 00:46:18,484
And I plan to tell them the truth

601
00:46:18,567 --> 00:46:21,487
even if that will hurt your feelings.

602
00:46:22,529 --> 00:46:25,407
I know. I'm prepared
to deal with the consequences.

603
00:46:26,074 --> 00:46:27,784
You should tell them the truth.

604
00:46:29,203 --> 00:46:32,456
I believe that this is the best thing
I can do for your sake.

605
00:46:33,707 --> 00:46:34,708
Yes.

606
00:46:39,588 --> 00:46:42,132
Jun-u, come to the counseling office.

607
00:46:51,391 --> 00:46:53,477
In addition to the allegation
of grade tampering,

608
00:46:53,685 --> 00:46:56,730
could we verify a few other things

609
00:46:57,231 --> 00:47:00,025
regarding your classmate,
Ma Hwi-yeong, with you?

610
00:47:01,777 --> 00:47:02,778
Sure.

611
00:47:08,283 --> 00:47:11,119
Are these allegations against him

612
00:47:11,787 --> 00:47:13,121
all true?

613
00:47:18,752 --> 00:47:20,003
Jun-u?

614
00:47:23,882 --> 00:47:24,800
Gosh.

615
00:47:25,676 --> 00:47:28,720
I really didn't think
Hwi-yeong would ever do such things.

616
00:47:28,804 --> 00:47:30,806
The fact that he rigged his grades
was shocking enough.

617
00:47:30,889 --> 00:47:32,558
I can't believe
he did the other things too.

618
00:47:32,641 --> 00:47:33,725
So-ye.

619
00:47:34,560 --> 00:47:36,311
Why didn't you tell us?

620
00:47:38,772 --> 00:47:40,440
I wish you had told me everything.

621
00:47:41,066 --> 00:47:43,277
I had no idea what Jun-u
was going through.

622
00:47:43,902 --> 00:47:45,988
I'm sorry. Back then,

623
00:47:46,321 --> 00:47:48,282
I was scared things would get out of hand.

624
00:47:48,365 --> 00:47:50,367
So-ye must have had her reasons.

625
00:47:55,539 --> 00:47:56,707
Soo-bin!

626
00:48:46,006 --> 00:48:48,300
Why didn't you tell me all this time

627
00:48:48,508 --> 00:48:50,177
what you were going through?

628
00:48:52,512 --> 00:48:54,640
Since I knew you'd be hurt.

629
00:48:55,641 --> 00:48:56,933
How could I tell you?

630
00:48:59,061 --> 00:49:00,187
Still...

631
00:49:00,937 --> 00:49:03,315
How did you deal with it all alone?

632
00:49:05,067 --> 00:49:06,902
Why didn't I find out earlier?

633
00:49:08,987 --> 00:49:11,531
Why didn't I even try to find out?

634
00:49:31,927 --> 00:49:32,969
Soo-bin.

635
00:49:35,889 --> 00:49:38,892
You and Hwi-yeong have been friends
since you were little.

636
00:49:41,103 --> 00:49:43,814
You must have hoped
Hwi-yeong wouldn't be such a person.

637
00:49:47,609 --> 00:49:50,696
You don't have to feel sorry.
I understand you.

638
00:49:52,155 --> 00:49:53,699
Don't blame yourself.

639
00:49:56,910 --> 00:49:58,078
I'll take care of it

640
00:50:00,956 --> 00:50:02,958
the way I want.

641
00:50:06,253 --> 00:50:07,254
Jun-u.

642
00:50:11,550 --> 00:50:13,510
How have you been enduring it all?

643
00:50:19,683 --> 00:50:20,726
Somehow.

644
00:50:22,602 --> 00:50:23,854
Thanks to you.

645
00:50:31,778 --> 00:50:32,863
Jun-u.

646
00:50:36,199 --> 00:50:39,619
It'll pass soon. This painful moment.

647
00:50:41,788 --> 00:50:42,831
Let's...

648
00:50:45,375 --> 00:50:46,710
endure it together.

649
00:50:59,723 --> 00:51:01,475
Your punishment

650
00:51:01,558 --> 00:51:04,394
for the grade tampering
will be decided soon.

651
00:51:05,103 --> 00:51:06,104
I see.

652
00:51:06,521 --> 00:51:09,232
Do you admit everything
regarding the incident

653
00:51:09,483 --> 00:51:10,776
with Choe Jun-u as well?

654
00:51:11,651 --> 00:51:12,652
Yes.

655
00:51:14,863 --> 00:51:16,698
I'm sure Jun-u told you everything.

656
00:51:17,157 --> 00:51:18,867
He put off answering the question.

657
00:51:28,001 --> 00:51:29,044
Jun-u.

658
00:51:31,254 --> 00:51:32,506
I'll give you a ride.

659
00:51:45,268 --> 00:51:46,478
I realized...

660
00:51:47,938 --> 00:51:49,314
something earlier.

661
00:51:51,399 --> 00:51:54,027
I haven't forgiven Hwi-yeong yet.

662
00:51:57,364 --> 00:52:01,243
Deep down, I still fiercely resent him.

663
00:52:05,831 --> 00:52:07,332
You've been holding up well.

664
00:52:09,334 --> 00:52:13,046
By the way, why did you
postpone an answer?

665
00:52:14,089 --> 00:52:16,508
You could have let it all out right there.

666
00:52:17,968 --> 00:52:19,845
Were you trying to hold back?

667
00:52:23,098 --> 00:52:25,141
That's why I hate myself even more.

668
00:52:27,727 --> 00:52:29,729
I don't know what I'm feeling right now.

669
00:52:32,941 --> 00:52:34,609
I hated him so much,

670
00:52:36,695 --> 00:52:38,780
and I still can't forgive him. But...

671
00:52:43,743 --> 00:52:45,537
But for some reason,
I couldn't say anything.

672
00:52:46,496 --> 00:52:48,123
I couldn't understand.

673
00:52:49,124 --> 00:52:50,709
I felt so stupid.

674
00:52:52,878 --> 00:52:54,337
Do you know why?

675
00:52:55,630 --> 00:52:57,549
It's because you're a nice person.

676
00:52:59,092 --> 00:53:01,553
You hesitate
because you're afraid to hurt someone

677
00:53:01,845 --> 00:53:04,389
with your anger and resentment.

678
00:53:04,973 --> 00:53:06,391
That's who you are.

679
00:53:12,314 --> 00:53:13,356
Jun-u.

680
00:53:14,858 --> 00:53:16,568
All you have to do is

681
00:53:16,985 --> 00:53:20,363
do what you think is right.

682
00:54:11,873 --> 00:54:13,041
Why did you do that?

683
00:54:16,086 --> 00:54:17,754
I have nothing to say.

684
00:54:19,673 --> 00:54:22,509
We've been best friends
since we were little.

685
00:54:23,093 --> 00:54:24,719
I can't believe...

686
00:54:26,388 --> 00:54:27,722
you did such a thing.

687
00:54:29,015 --> 00:54:30,558
I've always been a bad person.

688
00:54:31,017 --> 00:54:32,394
You know what?

689
00:54:34,187 --> 00:54:36,189
What hurts me the most is

690
00:54:37,190 --> 00:54:39,526
that even while saying
you're my best friend,

691
00:54:39,943 --> 00:54:42,278
I had no idea until now.

692
00:54:44,823 --> 00:54:46,866
That I just let you

693
00:54:48,368 --> 00:54:49,869
turn into this person.

694
00:54:51,621 --> 00:54:52,872
I'm sorry, Soo-bin.

695
00:54:53,832 --> 00:54:55,208
I might have...

696
00:54:57,460 --> 00:54:58,628
felt it

697
00:54:59,587 --> 00:55:01,423
at some point,

698
00:55:02,757 --> 00:55:04,467
although I wasn't sure.

699
00:55:05,719 --> 00:55:07,637
I probably hoped...

700
00:55:10,015 --> 00:55:11,683
you weren't such a person.

701
00:55:15,270 --> 00:55:17,564
I might have been scared
to know the truth.

702
00:55:18,648 --> 00:55:20,442
That's what I regret the most.

703
00:55:21,985 --> 00:55:23,069
No.

704
00:55:23,778 --> 00:55:25,822
You've been a great friend to me.

705
00:55:32,412 --> 00:55:33,455
I have to go.

706
00:55:53,641 --> 00:55:54,934
I'm home.

707
00:55:56,269 --> 00:55:59,272
Hi. How was the academy?

708
00:55:59,647 --> 00:56:00,648
Good.

709
00:56:01,191 --> 00:56:03,610
-I want some water.
-Sure.

710
00:56:09,491 --> 00:56:10,533
Soo-bin.

711
00:56:15,038 --> 00:56:16,790
Are the things about Hwi-yeong true?

712
00:56:17,332 --> 00:56:19,584
What about the thing with Jun-u?

713
00:56:36,434 --> 00:56:38,061
Mom, do you see now?

714
00:56:38,978 --> 00:56:40,855
Jun-u is not a bad kid.

715
00:56:41,481 --> 00:56:42,941
He's a good one.

716
00:56:55,245 --> 00:56:56,246
Mom.

717
00:56:59,082 --> 00:57:02,210
As you said, my grades have improved,

718
00:57:02,502 --> 00:57:05,130
and I've proven
that I can do well on my own.

719
00:57:05,797 --> 00:57:07,465
So can you trust me now?

720
00:57:08,299 --> 00:57:09,300
Soo-bin.

721
00:57:10,468 --> 00:57:11,803
I trust you.

722
00:57:16,141 --> 00:57:18,726
But it's a very important period
for you right now.

723
00:57:21,271 --> 00:57:22,272
Also,

724
00:57:23,189 --> 00:57:24,524
although you think

725
00:57:25,650 --> 00:57:28,194
you can do everything well on your own,

726
00:57:29,320 --> 00:57:31,448
at your age, nothing goes your way.

727
00:57:32,198 --> 00:57:35,618
Even you don't know
what you're feeling at that age.

728
00:57:35,702 --> 00:57:37,454
Just trust me for now.

729
00:57:37,829 --> 00:57:38,830
No matter what.

730
00:57:40,707 --> 00:57:43,960
Don't imagine anything
or make any assumptions.

731
00:57:46,963 --> 00:57:49,507
Nothing bad will happen to me.

732
00:57:50,884 --> 00:57:52,135
Jun-u also...

733
00:57:53,344 --> 00:57:55,305
improved his grades a lot this time,

734
00:57:56,306 --> 00:57:58,141
and he tried really hard.

735
00:58:00,268 --> 00:58:02,187
He's found what he wants to do...

736
00:58:06,065 --> 00:58:08,067
and we both tried so hard.

737
00:58:11,905 --> 00:58:13,448
We'll continue to try hard too.

738
00:58:15,783 --> 00:58:17,076
I just wanted to say that.

739
00:58:17,911 --> 00:58:19,120
I'll go to my room then.

740
00:58:41,893 --> 00:58:42,894
Soo-bin.

741
00:58:44,145 --> 00:58:46,439
I came to pick you up today.

742
00:58:46,523 --> 00:58:48,399
You know, you came to see me all the time.

743
00:58:49,984 --> 00:58:51,653
Come on, it's okay.

744
00:58:52,111 --> 00:58:53,029
Let's go.

745
00:59:02,372 --> 00:59:04,415
You can tell us comfortably.

746
00:59:05,583 --> 00:59:06,584
Okay.

747
00:59:13,716 --> 00:59:14,926
I won't...

748
00:59:16,344 --> 00:59:18,263
make any more statements.

749
00:59:26,020 --> 00:59:29,357
Please just investigate things
based on Hwi-yeong's statements.

750
00:59:37,282 --> 00:59:38,324
Jun-u.

751
00:59:45,790 --> 00:59:47,041
Soo-bin, I...

752
00:59:53,631 --> 00:59:54,882
You don't have to tell me.

753
00:59:56,843 --> 00:59:58,553
Whatever decision you made,

754
00:59:59,429 --> 01:00:00,763
you are right.

755
01:00:04,267 --> 01:00:05,351
Good job.

756
01:00:25,204 --> 01:00:27,749
DROPOUT APPLICATION FORM

757
01:00:32,003 --> 01:00:33,087
Hwi-yeong.

758
01:00:35,673 --> 01:00:37,175
You want to drop out of school?

759
01:00:40,595 --> 01:00:42,930
I want to leave this school
as soon as possible.

760
01:00:46,976 --> 01:00:47,977
But this...

761
01:00:50,355 --> 01:00:51,439
For now,

762
01:00:52,231 --> 01:00:57,278
why don't you take some time
and think about it, okay?

763
01:01:08,289 --> 01:01:09,666
I'll drop out.

764
01:01:12,460 --> 01:01:13,503
Hwi-yeong.

765
01:01:14,379 --> 01:01:16,422
This isn't the right way, okay?

766
01:01:16,506 --> 01:01:17,840
I'm sorry, Mr. Oh.

767
01:01:28,518 --> 01:01:29,519
Jun-u.

768
01:01:37,568 --> 01:01:39,404
You should've told them
everything about me.

769
01:01:40,738 --> 01:01:41,864
Why did you do that?

770
01:01:46,369 --> 01:01:48,955
I don't think I have to explain that
to you.

771
01:01:56,629 --> 01:01:57,964
I'm going to drop out of school.

772
01:02:18,234 --> 01:02:19,402
Hwi-yeong.

773
01:02:26,200 --> 01:02:28,453
Drop out of school? Who said you can?

774
01:02:29,454 --> 01:02:31,622
Why? Does that disappoint you?

775
01:02:32,248 --> 01:02:34,292
Because you forgave me
but I'm just running away?

776
01:02:34,375 --> 01:02:35,626
Who says I forgave you?

777
01:02:37,253 --> 01:02:39,589
Do you think I didn't say anything
because I forgave you?

778
01:02:40,840 --> 01:02:43,968
How could I forgive you
when you don't even regret what you did?

779
01:02:44,761 --> 01:02:46,262
Then what should I do?

780
01:02:46,345 --> 01:02:49,182
I'm giving up everything and leaving.

781
01:02:49,390 --> 01:02:50,975
This is the best way I can think of.

782
01:02:51,350 --> 01:02:53,394
I'm scared and afraid as well.

783
01:02:54,395 --> 01:02:56,147
What do I have to do then?

784
01:02:57,690 --> 01:02:59,025
What should I do?

785
01:03:03,196 --> 01:03:06,199
Have you ever been genuinely sorry
for what you did to me?

786
01:03:08,075 --> 01:03:09,827
From the bottom of your heart.

787
01:03:17,502 --> 01:03:19,003
You've never been sorry.

788
01:03:22,048 --> 01:03:24,300
The only thing that's important to you
is your pride.

789
01:03:28,012 --> 01:03:29,013
Ma Hwi-yeong.

790
01:03:33,476 --> 01:03:35,311
You haven't been forgiven.

791
01:03:37,438 --> 01:03:39,440
And yet, you're just running away...

792
01:03:41,734 --> 01:03:43,194
like a coward.

793
01:03:51,619 --> 01:03:52,703
Choe Jun-u!

794
01:04:07,927 --> 01:04:09,011
I'm sorry.

795
01:04:36,622 --> 01:04:37,707
I'm sorry.

796
